{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17536192","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17536192"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T17:04:29+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T17:04:29+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15627"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15627","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15627"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.76,0.03,0.08,0.05,0.07]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8318"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70576"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8318","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8318"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15627"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56040"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"11"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"27"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"483"},{"type":"tags","id":"1936"},{"type":"tags","id":"2220"},{"type":"tags","id":"4174"},{"type":"tags","id":"4976"},{"type":"tags","id":"4982"},{"type":"tags","id":"8118"},{"type":"tags","id":"8979"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11635"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20073"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23652"},{"type":"contributions","id":"30625"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43589"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70576","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/70576"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 52-year-old man presents to the General Practice clinic with progressive shortness of breath over two years. He reports increasing difficulty keeping up with his grandchildren and needs to stop after climbing one flight of stairs. He has worked in various underground mines including coal, copper, and gold for 25 years. He has chronic back pain but no other significant medical history. He has never smoked. He takes no regular medications.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, he appears well. His pulse rate is 82/min, blood pressure 128/78 mmHg, respiratory rate 20/min, SpO2 94% on room air, and temperature 36.8\u00b0C. His chest is hyperexpanded with decreased breath sounds throughout and prolonged expiration. There are no added sounds. Chest X-ray shows hyperinflation and upper zone nodular opacities.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Mixed dust pneumoconiosis","Non-specific interstitial pneumonia","Alpha-1 antitrypsin deficiency","Ankylosing spondylitis associated ILD","Sarcoidosis"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with features of respiratory disease in the context of significant occupational exposure to multiple types of mineral dusts. The absence of smoking history makes primary smoking-related lung disease unlikely. \u003Cstrong\u003EMixed dust pneumoconiosis\u003C/strong\u003E is the most likely diagnosis given his 25-year history of working in various types of mines and characteristic chest X-ray findings of upper zone nodular opacities.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESarcoidosis\u003C/strong\u003E can present with upper zone nodular opacities and breathlessness, but typically affects younger adults and often has associated features such as erythema nodosum or uveitis, which are not present here.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAlpha-1 antitrypsin deficiency\u003C/strong\u003E can cause early-onset emphysema, typically in the fourth or fifth decade. However, it characteristically affects the lower lobes and would be unusual without a family history.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAnkylosing spondylitis associated ILD\u003C/strong\u003E can cause respiratory symptoms and while the patient has back pain, there are no other features suggestive of ankylosing spondylitis such as morning stiffness or reduced spinal mobility. The radiological pattern would also be different.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENon-specific interstitial pneumonia\u003C/strong\u003E typically presents with restrictive rather than obstructive lung disease, with fine crackles on auscultation and different radiological findings. It is also more commonly associated with connective tissue diseases.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EMixed dust pneumoconiosis occurs in workers exposed to various types of mineral dusts including coal, silica, and metal dusts. The diagnosis is based on occupational history and radiological findings. Prevention through dust control measures and appropriate personal protective equipment is crucial.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Mixed dust pneumoconiosis can occur in workers exposed to multiple types of mineral dusts","Occupational history is crucial in evaluating respiratory disease","Chest X-ray changes may lag behind clinical symptoms in occupational lung disease"],"references":["Coggon D, Taylor AN. Coal mining and chronic obstructive pulmonary disease: a review of the evidence. Thorax. 1998 May 1;53(5):398\u2013407.","\u200c"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56040"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15627"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56040","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/56040"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-15T21:20:22+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-16T11:04:01+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8318"}},"content":{"data":{"